{"lemma":"فِرارُ","slug":"فِرارُ","root":"ف.ر.ر","root_slug":"ف-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فِرار","root":"فرر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33318","n33324"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَّ (farra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"escape"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flight"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fi.raːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33318","headword_ar":"فُرَارٌ","root":"fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faryrN","text_ar":"فَريرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young one of the ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the she-goat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the wild cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, T, S, M, O, K,) as also, in this last sense, (O, K,) and in the first and second senses, (K,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furofurN","text_ar":"فُرْفُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furofuwrN","text_ar":"فُرْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwrN","text_ar":"فَرُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAfirN","text_ar":"فُرَافِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or they [app. referring to all the foregoing words] signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lambs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [but see what follows:]) the female is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaArapN","text_ar":"فُرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaArN","text_ar":"فُرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. also; (T, M, K;) i. e. it is applied to a pl. number as well as to one; (TA;) it is said to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyrN","text_ar":"فَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, O;) and is of a rare form of pl.; (A 'Obeyd, S, O, K; *) and it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small in body of the young ones of the goat-kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyrN","text_ar":"فَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as some say, signifies thus: (TA: [but this I think doubtful:]) this last word is said by IAar to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young one of the wild animal, of the gazelle"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bovine kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in one instance he says that it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lambs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and, (T, A,) as Aboo-l-'Abbás [i. e. Th] states on the authority of IAar, (T,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaArN","text_ar":"فُرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaArapN","text_ar":"فُرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyrN","text_ar":"فَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fururN","text_ar":"فُرُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furofuwrN","text_ar":"فُرْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAfirN","text_ar":"فُرَافِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M) signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamb when it is weaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has become what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaforN","text_ar":"جَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and obtained plenty of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has become fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M:) accord. to Ibn-'Abbád, (O,) the last two signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lamb"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamal","text_ar":"حَمَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", O, TA, in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamal","text_ar":"جَمَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", a mistranscription, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it eats, and chews the cud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furofuwrN","text_ar":"فُرْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below:]) and [it is also said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaArN","text_ar":"فُرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahom","text_ar":"بَهْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lambs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kids"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and one thereof is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furofuwrN","text_ar":"فُرْفُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said in a prov."},{"kind":"quote","text":"nazowu AlfuraAri A@sotajohala AlfuraAraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The leaping of the wild calf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or with equal propriety"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfrAr","text_ar":"الفرار"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kid, excited to lightness the"},{"kind":"text","text":"other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild calf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kid"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, S, O, K:) A 'Obeyd says, on the authority of El-Mu- ärrij, [and so says Meyd, and the same is implied in the S and O,] that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfrAr","text_ar":"الفرار"},{"kind":"text","text":"here means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the young one of the wild cow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) i. e., when the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frAr","text_ar":"فرار"},{"kind":"text","text":"attains to youthful vigour it takes to leaping, and when another sees it [do so] it leaps in like manner: (T, S, K:) the prov. is used in relation to him of whose companionship one should be cautious; meaning, if thou become his companion thou wilt do as he does: (T, O, K:) some relate it otherwise, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazowa","text_ar":"نَزْوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazaA nazowa AlfuraAri","text_ar":"نَزَا نَزْوَ الفُرَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) [See also a similar prov. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sfh","text_ar":"سفه"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 5.]"}],"source_refs":["M","K","O","T","A","S"]},{"entry_id":"n33324","headword_ar":"فَرَّارٌ","root":"fr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAr~N","text_ar":"فَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Quicksilver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because flowing quickly, and not remaining in a place: thus says Esh-Shereeshee. (Har p. 139.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}